CatDescriptText: Miss Lizzie Bundridge, 3611 Whitney Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 18, 1958, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think the Federal Government should immediately enforce the Supreme Court's recent decision in 'Little Rock School Case' or permit the recalcitrant states to take their time in obeying?" answer reads: "My feeling is that the Federal Government should do something about the situation because the states are going to take time because they are not in favor of it."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Lizzie Bundridge wearing hoop earrings, dark coat, and wristwatch, holding bags and checkered books titled "Pittsburgh Institution for Savings... Pittsburgh Home Savings" standing on sidewalk with two men in front of light colored stone building
